I can confirm this issue issue -- the SDK AARs are missing consumer ProGuard rules, causing R8 to strip classes that are needed at runtime.

Workaround (works now): Add these rules to your proguard-rules.pro:

-keep class com.facebook.** { *; }
-keep class com.meta.** { *; }
-keepattributes Signature  # Required for Gson TypeToken
-keep class * extends com.google.protobuf.GeneratedMessageLite { *; }



Looking at this now!

@bddckr Thank you for the great feedback! This is very helpful.

This is a confirmed issue -- when android:value="0" is used in your manifest, Android stores it as an integer internally, but the SDK reads it as a string, which returns null.

Working on updating this!

@bddckr Good news — SDK v0.6.0 is now available and includes the fix for this issue. The fix creates a fresh session for each permission check, which addresses both the post-registration INTERNAL_ERROR and the sporadic BLE reconnect case you described.

To resolve: Please upgrade to SDK v0.6.0. The INTERNAL_ERROR on checkPermissionStatus() and the reset() permanence issue should both be resolved. You should no longer need to call reset() as a workaround.

Let us know how it goes!
